<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <title>TestOrg Security Dashboard</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
    <script src="ws.js" defer></script>
    
</head>

<body>

    <nav class="top-nav">
    <a href="index.html">Dashboard</a>
    
    <a href="orphans.html">Orphans (1)</a>
    <a href="report.html" class="nav-right">Report</a>
    <a href="deleted.html">Deleted (0)</a>
    <a href="admin.html" class="admin-link">Admin</a>
</nav>

    <div class="page-header">
        <p class="meta"><strong>Date:</strong> 2026-04-09 12:00 UTC · <strong>Scope:</strong> 1 total · 1 non-archived · 0 archived repositories in <code>TestOrg</code></p>
    </div>

    <div class="scorecard">
        <div class="card health-score-card tier-warn" title="Geometric mean of measured control rates across six controls — Security Policy, Secret Scanning, Dependabot, Branch Protection, CODEOWNERS, Archival Coverage. Unmeasured controls are excluded from each rate's denominator. Rewards balanced improvement across all controls.">
            <p class="card-label">Org Governance</p>
            <p class="card-value">68.8%</p>
            <div class="progress-bar">
                <div class="progress-fill tier-warn w-70"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card tier-warn" title="Percentage of public repos with a SECURITY.md or GitHub security-policy setting enabled.">
            <p class="card-label">Security Policy <span class="tooltip-trigger" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Add a SECURITY.md file to the repo root, .github/, or docs/ — or use the Security tab&#39;s Reporting → Security policy → Start setup for a guided pull request.">ⓘ</span></p>
            <p class="card-value">66.7% (2/3)</p>
            <div class="progress-bar">
                <div class="progress-fill tier-warn w-65"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card tier-warn" title="Percentage of repos with Dependabot security updates enabled (auto-PRs for vulnerable dependencies).">
            <p class="card-label">Dependabot Status <span class="tooltip-trigger" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Enable it under Settings → Security → Advanced Security: click Enable next to Dependabot alerts (this also governs Dependabot security updates), or apply it org-wide via a security configuration.">ⓘ</span></p>
            <p class="card-value">60.0% (3/5)</p>
            <div class="progress-bar">
                <div class="progress-fill tier-warn w-60"></div>
            </div>
            <p class="card-detail">1 unmeasured (1 unknown)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card tier-pass" title="Percentage of public repos with GitHub secret scanning enabled to detect leaked credentials.">
            <p class="card-label">Secret Scanning <span class="tooltip-trigger" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Enable it under Settings → Security → Advanced Security: click Enable → Enable Secret Protection next to Secret Protection (turns on scanning and push protection together). Counts public repositories only, mirroring the organisation-wide Secret Scanning figure.">ⓘ</span></p>
            <p class="card-value">80.0% (4/5)</p>
            <p class="card-detail">0 open org alerts · success</p>
            <div class="progress-bar">
                <div
                    class="progress-fill tier-pass w-80">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <a href="branch_protection.html" class="card tier-warn" title="Percentage of observable repos at branch-protection BPR2 (IntegrityOnly) or higher. Unreadable or permission-suspected repos are excluded from this percentage (see the unmeasured breakdown below), not classified as below-bar. Click through for the BPR0..BPR5 regime drill-down.">
            <p class="card-label">Branch Protection <span class="tooltip-trigger" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Add a branch protection rule (Settings → Branches) or ruleset (Settings → Rules → Rulesets) on the default branch: require PR review, disallow force-push and deletion, and disable bypass so admins can&#39;t skip it.">ⓘ</span></p>
            <p class="card-value">60.0% (3/5)</p>
            <p class="card-detail">BPR1 0 · 1 unmeasured (1 unknown)</p>
            <div class="progress-bar">
                <div
                    class="progress-fill tier-warn w-60">
                </div>
            </div>
        </a>
        <div class="card tier-pass" title="Percentage of repos with a CODEOWNERS file identifying responsible teams or individuals.">
            <p class="card-label">CODEOWNERS <span class="tooltip-trigger" tabindex="0" data-tooltip="Add .github/CODEOWNERS naming a GitHub team (not an individual) with write access to the repo, e.g. `*   @your-org/team-slug` — teams survive membership changes.">ⓘ</span></p>
            <p class="card-value">80.0% (4/5)</p>
            <div class="progress-bar">
                <div class="progress-fill tier-pass w-80"></div>
            </div>
            <p class="card-detail">1 unmeasured (1 unknown)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card tier-na" title="Archived / (archived + stale-active) — fraction of stale-lifecycle repos that have been archived. Stale = no update in 2+ years. Higher is better.">
            <p class="card-label">Archival Coverage</p>
            <p class="card-value">N/A (0/0)</p>
            <p class="card-detail">0 archived · 0 stale</p>
            <div class="progress-bar">
                <div class="progress-fill tier-na w-0"></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    

</body>

</html>
